title: MAFS' couple Nick and Sharon spotted in Sydney | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 354 shares With her blonde locks glamorously curled, Sharon showed off her slender figure in a pair of tight black jeans and a white crop top. She completed her look with a pair of black lace-up heels, wheeling a carry-on luggage as she walked along with her twin by her side. Marital bliss? 31-year-old Sharon appeared upbeat as she stepped out in Sydney with her TV husband Going strong? The Western Australia-based beauty was grinning from ear to ear while standing next to the carpenter Nick meanwhile, cut a casual figure in a pair of black jeans and a blue T-shirt as he walked alongside Sharon. The Victoria-based hunk was carrying a backpack, and took turns wheeling the luggage with Sharon. The pair seemed friendly as they stopped by the side of the road for a chat, with Sharon grinning from ear to ear. Matching: The reality couple both wore black jeans for the outing, with Sharon showing off her figure in a white crop top Part of the family? Nick cut a casual figure as he walked alongside Sharon and her twin sister Reality romance: Sharon and Nick tied the knot on Tuesday night's episode of the Channel Nine show Sharon, who is the older of the twins, was delighted when she met Nick for the first time on Monday night's episode. The Western Australia-based beauty revealed she was hoping for a country boy, saying before the wedding: 'I hope my guy is from the country. They've got a different aura. A different way of holding themselves and a different way of coming across. I find that really attractive.' Luckily for Sharon, Nick was everything she had hoped for, with the hunk describing himself as 'a country boy at heart'. Just her luck: Older twin Sharon was immediately thrilled with her match, while sister Michelle didn't feel the same connection with her groom Jesse What a girl wants: Sharon revealed prior to meeting Nick that she wanted a country boy who is loyal Right for her? Nick was everything Sharon had hoped for, after telling the blonde he is a 'country boy at heart' 'Sharon. I thought 'wow' absolutely gorgeous girl, seriously. I'm so lucky,' Nick said upon meeting his bride 'Tall, dark, handsome. Blue eyes, oh my god. I gotta say I'm pretty happy,' Sharon said, upon meeting her match. 'Sharon. I thought 'wow' absolutely gorgeous girl, seriously. I'm so lucky. I definitely felt a little bit insecure. She was probably a little bit too good for me,' Nick added. The pair's chemistry was undeniable, with Sharon gushing: 'Nick definitely makes me feel at ease. It feels comfortable. It feels really right.' Unlucky in love? Meanwhile, Sharon's sister Michelle confessed she was 'worried' about her match with Jesse, admitting she didn't feel the 'chemistry' Double trouble: The 31-year-old twins walked down the aisle in an Australian TV first, tying the knot with two complete strangers at the same time The grooms: Nick and Jesse were shocked to see that they were sharing a wedding ceremony 'Tall, dark, handsome. Blue eyes, oh my god. I gotta say I'm pretty happy,' Sharon said of her groom Nick Meanwhile, Sharon's sister Michelle wasn't so taken by her groom Jesse. 'Right now I'm a little bit worried. The sexual chemistry is not there. I don't know what to do,' Michelle said after locking lips with the retailer during the ceremony. 31-year-old Jesse clearly had mixed signals from his bride, admitting: 'I felt like a bit of a spark. Like it could go somewhere. I hope so. I hope we're gonna do some more kissing later.'
